WEBVTT

1
00:00:20.529 --> 00:00:22.531
TSINGHUA UNIVERSITY

2
00:00:24.867 --> 00:00:25.868
Li!

3
00:00:28.287 --> 00:00:29.830
- Good morning.
- Morning.


4
00:00:30.498 --> 00:00:33.042
- Have a bite.
- I'm not hungry.


5
00:00:33.125 --> 00:00:36.879
Breakfast is the most
important meal of the day.


6
00:00:36.962 --> 00:00:39.423
- Okay.
- Come on.


7
00:00:39.507 --> 00:00:41.091
It's too early
for you two to act so lovey-dovey.


8
00:00:43.677 --> 00:00:44.720
Jun!

9
00:00:49.517 --> 00:00:50.935
At least you remembered this time.

10
00:00:51.018 --> 00:00:53.145
It's not funny! 
I just forgot about it.

11
00:00:54.814 --> 00:00:56.899
- Ah, this trick again?
- Go!


12
00:01:01.487 --> 00:01:04.031
- You guys are too slow!
- We'll see.


13
00:01:05.324 --> 00:01:08.452
- Go! Go!
- We're winning!


14
00:01:08.536 --> 00:01:10.287
Come on!

15
00:01:10.371 --> 00:01:11.372
Go!

16
00:01:22.424 --> 00:01:23.425
- Hi.
- Hi.


17
00:01:23.509 --> 00:01:26.262
- It's a pleasure to meet you, Mr. Davis.
- You can call me Daniel.


18
00:01:26.345 --> 00:01:28.430
Are you the assistant they hired?

19
00:01:28.514 --> 00:01:29.807
- Yes, and I'm so grateful...
- Great.


20
00:01:29.890 --> 00:01:31.225
...to have the chance to work with you.

21
00:01:31.308 --> 00:01:33.394
- Yeah.
- I've read so much of your work.


22
00:01:33.477 --> 00:01:36.272
It's really remarkable.
The coverage of '89 in particular.


23
00:01:36.355 --> 00:01:38.190
Uh, no, I don't do
that sort of thing anymore.


24
00:01:38.524 --> 00:01:40.067
Well, the writing was excellent.

25
00:01:41.026 --> 00:01:42.862
I can't tell you how much
I've learned from you already.


26
00:01:42.945 --> 00:01:44.822
- Where'd you park?
- Reading your student interviews


27
00:01:44.905 --> 00:01:47.199
- in particular was so educational...
- What'd you say your name was again?


28
00:01:47.283 --> 00:01:48.742
- Min.
- Min. So nice to meet you.


29
00:01:48.826 --> 00:01:50.703
We'll have plenty of time
to talk about writing later.


30
00:01:50.786 --> 00:01:52.371
But I want to get the hell out
of this airport.


31
00:01:52.454 --> 00:01:54.164
I've been on a plane for 16 hours.

32
00:01:54.248 --> 00:01:56.208
- Of course, of course, this way.
- Yeah. Okay.


33
00:02:03.799 --> 00:02:06.135
Jun, why haven't you left yet?

34
00:02:08.220 --> 00:02:10.931
You look so pretty today.

35
00:02:11.015 --> 00:02:12.516
I wanted to keep watching.

36
00:02:12.600 --> 00:02:15.603
So sweet all of a sudden.

37
00:02:15.686 --> 00:02:17.938
I can't believe you get up early
every day for this.


38
00:02:18.606 --> 00:02:20.274
What's the point?

39
00:02:20.357 --> 00:02:22.276
It's good for the mind and body.

40
00:02:22.359 --> 00:02:23.402
Let me show you.

41
00:02:26.780 --> 00:02:29.116
Falun Gong has five sets of exercises.

42
00:02:29.199 --> 00:02:31.785
It takes two hours to do them.

43
00:02:32.369 --> 00:02:33.203
That's it?

44
00:02:34.330 --> 00:02:37.249
Well, the movements are easy to learn.
But the key is to follow the principles


45
00:02:37.333 --> 00:02:39.627
of Truth, Compassion, and Tolerance.
That's not so easy.


46
00:02:40.169 --> 00:02:41.545
You think you can handle it?

47
00:02:42.338 --> 00:02:44.298
- Of course.
- Give it a try?


48
00:02:44.381 --> 00:02:47.301
- Okay.
- Let's get started.


49
00:03:11.116 --> 00:03:13.118
FALUN GONG FREE TEACHING

50
00:03:17.748 --> 00:03:18.791
What do you think of this?

51
00:03:20.876 --> 00:03:22.419
Falun Gong?

52
00:03:23.295 --> 00:03:24.797
It's certainly popular.

53
00:03:25.714 --> 00:03:27.675
It seems like everyone
is a practitioner these days.


54
00:03:28.968 --> 00:03:30.010
100 million.

55
00:03:31.345 --> 00:03:34.098
Wow. They have
more members than the Party!


56
00:03:46.235 --> 00:03:49.655
Do something. Secretary Yang
has an important meeting to get to.


57
00:03:53.909 --> 00:03:54.785
Yes, sir.

58
00:04:10.718 --> 00:04:12.261
You! Move up.

59
00:04:12.344 --> 00:04:13.887
Get out of here.

60
00:04:19.560 --> 00:04:21.478
Keep moving.

61
00:04:42.541 --> 00:04:43.834
Are you trying to electrocute me?

62
00:04:44.668 --> 00:04:45.502
Wait.

63
00:04:46.503 --> 00:04:48.047
The results from the beta test are back.

64
00:04:55.012 --> 00:04:57.097
I don't think our system
can produce these results.


65
00:04:59.475 --> 00:05:02.144
Everybody tweaks their data.

66
00:05:02.478 --> 00:05:03.479
No one will be able to tell.

67
00:05:04.146 --> 00:05:05.647
But we are lying.

68
00:05:07.483 --> 00:05:10.235
If we submit the real results,
we won't get the grant.


69
00:05:10.861 --> 00:05:15.240
Now that you're practicing,
you have to be honest.


70
00:05:17.367 --> 00:05:18.494
All right.

71
00:05:20.913 --> 00:05:23.499
Oh, yes!

72
00:05:24.792 --> 00:05:27.169
- I can't eat anything anymore, Mr. Gao!
- Yes.


73
00:05:27.252 --> 00:05:28.462
You're going to feed me to death!

74
00:05:28.545 --> 00:05:30.089
Come on, no, we're just getting started.

75
00:05:30.172 --> 00:05:32.424
I've got ten years to make up for.

76
00:05:32.508 --> 00:05:35.844
I knew I missed this man
for a reason.


77
00:05:39.223 --> 00:05:41.725
I'm just curious.
Why did you take this job?


78
00:05:43.143 --> 00:05:45.229
I think it was
your coverage of June 4th.

79
00:05:45.312 --> 00:05:46.313
Oh.

80
00:05:47.397 --> 00:05:49.066
You stood up for something

81
00:05:49.149 --> 00:05:52.361
and you took a risk to give
a voice to those students.


82
00:05:52.444 --> 00:05:54.113
The student I interviewed was killed.

83
00:05:55.447 --> 00:05:56.281
Did you know that?

84
00:05:57.866 --> 00:05:59.201
I suppose I assumed.

85
00:05:59.993 --> 00:06:02.704
I'm sure to you, right now,
journalism feels like


86
00:06:03.580 --> 00:06:06.458
the most urgent work a person can do.

87
00:06:08.127 --> 00:06:09.211
But the world forgets.

88
00:06:10.295 --> 00:06:11.463
And forgets quickly.

89
00:06:16.969 --> 00:06:19.638
Our lab was denied the grant.

90
00:06:20.764 --> 00:06:23.600
Something wrong with the data, I heard.

91
00:06:24.268 --> 00:06:28.564
You know I am a Falun Gong practitioner.

92
00:06:29.189 --> 00:06:30.732
I can't abandon truth
just for convenience.


93
00:06:31.483 --> 00:06:33.318
I have heard rumors.

94
00:06:34.820 --> 00:06:39.324
The higher-ups may take
action against Falun Gong.


95
00:06:40.284 --> 00:06:41.994
You have to be careful.

96
00:06:42.077 --> 00:06:43.328
That's impossible.

97
00:06:43.829 --> 00:06:45.539
The government has been very supportive.

98
00:06:45.622 --> 00:06:46.790
Many Party members practice.

99
00:06:46.874 --> 00:06:48.876
That's exactly the issue.

100
00:06:50.586 --> 00:06:52.588
Falun Gong teaches us
to be a good person.

101
00:06:52.671 --> 00:06:54.798
The more people who practice,
the better, right?


102
00:07:00.929 --> 00:07:02.764
Maybe I overreacted.

103
00:07:05.017 --> 00:07:08.604
All right, I'll let you go.

104
00:07:10.689 --> 00:07:11.565
Okay.

105
00:07:42.387 --> 00:07:46.183
It's clearly getting out of control.

106
00:07:46.266 --> 00:07:50.187
Secretary Yang,
the Party is counting on you.


107
00:07:58.320 --> 00:07:59.863
I pulled an all-nighter.

108
00:08:02.950 --> 00:08:04.868
What's going on?

109
00:08:08.080 --> 00:08:09.164
What happened?

110
00:08:09.248 --> 00:08:10.666
You're so late today.

111
00:08:11.500 --> 00:08:14.544
Dozens of practitioners were
arrested and beaten in Tianjin.


112
00:08:14.628 --> 00:08:15.629
What?

113
00:08:15.712 --> 00:08:17.214
This has to be a misunderstanding.

114
00:08:17.673 --> 00:08:21.468
The Tianjin government
told the practitioners to come to Beijing.


115
00:08:21.551 --> 00:08:23.178
Why come to Beijing?

116
00:08:24.763 --> 00:08:29.101
We should go to the Appeals Office
and file an appeal.


117
00:08:29.184 --> 00:08:31.353
Yes, yes, let's go!

118
00:08:31.436 --> 00:08:33.814
I don't think it's that simple.

119
00:08:34.523 --> 00:08:36.858
My father's unit participated
in the crackdown in '89.


120
00:08:36.942 --> 00:08:40.696
He warned me to stay
away from this sort of thing.


121
00:08:40.779 --> 00:08:42.197
We're good people.

122
00:08:42.281 --> 00:08:44.533
What do we have to worry about?

123
00:08:47.828 --> 00:08:51.164
We want to report the situation
to the Appeals Office.


124
00:08:51.248 --> 00:08:54.042
- Anybody want to go?
- Sure, yes.


125
00:08:54.835 --> 00:08:56.712
Okay. Let's go.

126
00:09:06.555 --> 00:09:08.515
There are so many people.

127
00:09:12.227 --> 00:09:13.812
Let's go to the gate.

128
00:09:27.993 --> 00:09:29.494
This is unbelievable.

129
00:09:31.121 --> 00:09:34.041
This has got to be the largest
demonstration since '89.


130
00:09:34.791 --> 00:09:35.751
So quiet.

131
00:09:37.044 --> 00:09:37.919
Hey!

132
00:09:38.628 --> 00:09:39.755
Come with me.

133
00:09:39.838 --> 00:09:42.049
Wait, wait, no. 
I'm allowed to be here.

134
00:09:42.132 --> 00:09:44.301
Sir, I have a
press pass. A press pass.

135
00:09:44.384 --> 00:09:46.803
- Doesn't matter, come with me now.
- You can't do that.


136
00:09:46.887 --> 00:09:48.180
I have credentials to be here.

137
00:09:51.641 --> 00:09:53.769
- Hello, everyone.
- Hello.


138
00:09:54.186 --> 00:09:56.188
I am from the Appeals Office.

139
00:09:57.689 --> 00:10:00.442
We would like to speak to your organizers.

140
00:10:03.195 --> 00:10:06.156
We have no organizers.
We've all come voluntarily.


141
00:10:06.239 --> 00:10:08.408
Some of you must volunteer.

142
00:10:08.492 --> 00:10:10.410
We cannot speak with all of you.

143
00:10:12.329 --> 00:10:13.372
I will go.

144
00:10:13.455 --> 00:10:14.498
And I.

145
00:10:14.581 --> 00:10:17.292
- I will go too.
- I will go too.


146
00:10:17.376 --> 00:10:18.377
I will go too.

147
00:10:19.127 --> 00:10:21.713
Fine. You five, come with me.

148
00:10:23.882 --> 00:10:26.051
Excuse me. Thank you.

149
00:10:34.226 --> 00:10:35.352
Please have a seat.

150
00:10:40.857 --> 00:10:44.945
We're here to find out
about the arrest in Tianjin.


151
00:10:45.737 --> 00:10:48.198
We're looking into this incident.

152
00:10:49.324 --> 00:10:51.410
There might be some misunderstanding...

153
00:11:15.058 --> 00:11:16.560
It's good to see you again, Daniel.

154
00:11:17.436 --> 00:11:19.271
I wasn't sure you'd be back.

155
00:11:19.354 --> 00:11:21.356
Neither was I.

156
00:11:22.566 --> 00:11:24.568
You've been away for a long time, Daniel.

157
00:11:25.318 --> 00:11:26.778
Many things have changed.

158
00:11:27.904 --> 00:11:29.364
Perhaps you have changed, too?

159
00:11:30.115 --> 00:11:32.284
Being hauled into a van

160
00:11:33.160 --> 00:11:34.911
in the middle of the night
and driven to the airport


161
00:11:34.995 --> 00:11:37.247
with no warning
will alter a person's worldview.


162
00:11:37.914 --> 00:11:39.458
But that's in the past.

163
00:11:39.916 --> 00:11:42.878
I came back to work on a book
about traditional Chinese culture.


164
00:11:42.961 --> 00:11:44.629
Our expectations are clear.

165
00:11:45.046 --> 00:11:46.173
You're a guest here.

166
00:11:46.256 --> 00:11:47.632
China is home to me.

167
00:11:48.091 --> 00:11:50.802
All the more reason
to highlight its triumphs.


168
00:11:58.143 --> 00:12:00.103
I don't see why
that would be an issue.

169
00:12:06.776 --> 00:12:08.153
Good to have you back.

170
00:12:10.280 --> 00:12:11.281
Thank you!

171
00:12:14.910 --> 00:12:17.078
Thank you for coming.

172
00:12:17.162 --> 00:12:20.749
Please tell everyone to go home.

173
00:12:20.832 --> 00:12:22.125
Of course.

174
00:12:24.753 --> 00:12:25.629
That's great!

175
00:12:33.386 --> 00:12:37.599
The officials have confirmed
that the government


176
00:12:37.682 --> 00:12:40.101
has never banned any kind of qigong.

177
00:12:40.185 --> 00:12:43.772
And they have assured us
the practitioners will be released.


178
00:12:43.855 --> 00:12:45.357
We can go home now.

179
00:12:57.619 --> 00:12:58.662
Great!

180
00:12:58.745 --> 00:13:00.622
All resolved.

181
00:13:00.705 --> 00:13:02.999
Let's go.

182
00:13:04.084 --> 00:13:06.836
On April 25, 1999

183
00:13:06.920 --> 00:13:09.339
over ten thousand Falun Gong members

184
00:13:09.422 --> 00:13:12.259
besieged the headquarters
of the Chinese Communist Party.


185
00:13:12.342 --> 00:13:15.095
It was a vicious attack against the Party.

186
00:13:15.178 --> 00:13:18.682
They severely interfered
with government operations


187
00:13:18.765 --> 00:13:21.643
and gravely disrupted social order.

188
00:13:21.726 --> 00:13:24.354
This is the most
serious political incident


189
00:13:24.437 --> 00:13:28.400
since the 1989 riots
in Tiananmen Square...


190
00:13:28.483 --> 00:13:29.651
What's going on?

191
00:13:31.903 --> 00:13:33.280
It was a trap.

192
00:13:33.363 --> 00:13:35.240
The government declares

193
00:13:35.323 --> 00:13:36.950
Falun Dafa Association
and Falun Gong illegal.


194
00:13:37.033 --> 00:13:37.909
Wang.

195
00:13:37.993 --> 00:13:39.786
They are officially banned.

196
00:13:39.869 --> 00:13:43.498
CHINESE COMMUNIST PARTY
CENTRAL COMMITTEE DIRECTIVE


197
00:13:46.334 --> 00:13:47.544
Get in the car!

198
00:13:47.627 --> 00:13:48.587
Move it!

199
00:13:49.879 --> 00:13:50.797
Hurry up.

200
00:14:05.979 --> 00:14:09.316
- Incredible, isn't it?
- It is...


201
00:14:10.275 --> 00:14:11.943
You seem unsure.

202
00:14:14.487 --> 00:14:17.824
Of course, I support the Party.

203
00:14:18.867 --> 00:14:20.619
I just wonder

204
00:14:20.702 --> 00:14:24.748
if Falun Gong is threatening
enough to warrant all of this.


205
00:14:30.003 --> 00:14:32.631
If Falun Gong wins the people's hearts,

206
00:14:33.548 --> 00:14:35.300
who will be left to follow the Party?

207
00:14:37.844 --> 00:14:39.679
Of course, of course.

208
00:14:42.807 --> 00:14:44.392
Opportunities like this

209
00:14:44.476 --> 00:14:45.644
don't come around often.

210
00:14:49.689 --> 00:14:51.316
It's up to you to
make the most of it.

211
00:15:14.923 --> 00:15:15.799
What's wrong?

212
00:15:16.841 --> 00:15:18.635
Jun? Jun?

213
00:15:21.096 --> 00:15:21.930
Wang.

214
00:15:23.181 --> 00:15:24.099
Come in.

215
00:15:42.951 --> 00:15:46.121
Wang, I know you're
under a lot of pressure.


216
00:15:47.288 --> 00:15:49.040
You are a bright star at Tsinghua.

217
00:15:51.000 --> 00:15:52.836
I won't make it difficult for you.

218
00:15:53.628 --> 00:15:54.629
Just sign this.

219
00:15:56.297 --> 00:15:57.465
Nobody needs to know.

220
00:15:58.466 --> 00:16:00.301
All of the trouble will be behind you.

221
00:16:15.483 --> 00:16:17.652
The Ministry of Education
has issued a directive.


222
00:16:17.736 --> 00:16:20.989
Anyone who refuses to denounce
Falun Gong will be expelled.


223
00:16:22.532 --> 00:16:24.492
You are about to complete your PhD.

224
00:16:25.034 --> 00:16:27.662
This is your life.
Think about it carefully.


225
00:16:28.955 --> 00:16:30.749
Everything here...

226
00:16:31.624 --> 00:16:36.004
It's all a lie. "Anti-science,
anti-human, and anti-society..."


227
00:16:36.713 --> 00:16:38.381
"I denounce and condemn Falun Gong."

228
00:16:39.299 --> 00:16:40.633
How can I possibly sign this?

229
00:16:42.719 --> 00:16:45.013
The Party has determined
the nature of Falun Gong.


230
00:16:45.096 --> 00:16:47.807
As a student Party leader,
you of all people should follow the Party.


231
00:16:47.891 --> 00:16:49.434
Secretary, will you tell the truth?

232
00:16:49.934 --> 00:16:54.022
The practitioners in our school, does
anyone fit the portrayal in the media?


233
00:16:54.773 --> 00:16:57.066
You are a Party
member and so am I.

234
00:16:57.942 --> 00:16:59.319
I dare to speak the truth.

235
00:17:00.820 --> 00:17:01.696
But you don't!

236
00:17:06.993 --> 00:17:10.663
Wang, who do you
think you are talking to?

237
00:17:13.541 --> 00:17:15.668
Secretary Wu,

238
00:17:17.504 --> 00:17:21.257
could we have a moment alone?

239
00:17:38.942 --> 00:17:39.901
Wang...

240
00:17:43.154 --> 00:17:47.617
...you are the age
my son was when he was killed.


241
00:17:48.785 --> 00:17:49.953
He was exactly like you.

242
00:17:51.412 --> 00:17:52.247
Smart

243
00:17:53.581 --> 00:17:54.666
and stubborn.

244
00:18:01.714 --> 00:18:02.549
I...

245
00:18:07.053 --> 00:18:11.099
I regret every day.

246
00:18:11.724 --> 00:18:14.143
He was pushing his bike out the door.

247
00:18:15.436 --> 00:18:18.106
I should have tried harder to stop him.

248
00:18:20.275 --> 00:18:22.694
Even if I had to break his legs

249
00:18:22.777 --> 00:18:24.946
and take care of him
for the rest of his life.


250
00:18:27.282 --> 00:18:28.199
So he was killed...

251
00:18:29.492 --> 00:18:31.828
- ...during the riot...?
- Riot?


252
00:18:31.911 --> 00:18:35.123
It was a peaceful appeal made by students.

253
00:18:35.206 --> 00:18:37.417
They labeled it a riot

254
00:18:37.500 --> 00:18:39.377
and launched a massacre.

255
00:18:40.753 --> 00:18:47.427
Now the Party is using the same
tactic against Falun Gong.


256
00:18:49.220 --> 00:18:50.138
I...

257
00:18:52.015 --> 00:18:55.143
I don't want to lose another son.

258
00:19:01.649 --> 00:19:03.318
It's just a formality.

259
00:19:04.277 --> 00:19:06.988
Nobody knows what you really believe.

260
00:19:07.822 --> 00:19:09.365
I would know!

261
